Here are the sources used, excluding the randomly found phrases/sentences in the test.big and test.small files.
I can email these to you with links attached because the link formatting is lost when pasted into a plaintext file.

For the text.language, I went to Project Gutenberg and tried to find a non-poem/play of that language (some languages are missing). For the wiki.language, I went to each language's region/country page, which I assume would have a lot of text (e.g. I took the Swedish page of the "Sweden" article).

For the test data, I used omniglot.com to pick some phrases for the language, and also chose random sentences from Wikipedia for the language. I do not know what most of the sentences say. I purposely chose some long and short phrases, assuming the short ones will be more difficult to identify.

